1
00:00:01,040 --> 00:00:02,400
我毁掉了你的文件
I destroyed your file. 

2
00:00:02,560 --> 00:00:04,400
但不确定那是唯一的一份
I can't be certain that's the only one they have.

3
00:00:04,560 --> 00:00:07,000
如果他们发现你有前科 肯定会撤销你的签证
If they find out you've got a history, they will revoke your visa

4
00:00:07,120 --> 00:00:08,800
然后遣送你回国
and they will send you home,

5
00:00:08,960 --> 00:00:11,360
有前科的人是不允许获得学习签证的
because people with histories don't get study visas.

6
00:00:11,520 --> 00:00:15,240
这是一个女人昨晚放在我们门口的
A woman left this at our door last night.

7
00:00:15,400 --> 00:00:18,047
在你被杀的那晚它就不见了 
Disappeared on the night you were murdered. 

8
00:00:18,048 --> 00:00:19,880
没想到现在又出现了
Now it's returned to me.

9
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,400
这女孩很漂亮呢
Pretty girl.

10
00:00:21,560 --> 00:00:23,000
你想让我找到她的档案
You wanted me to find her file.

11
00:00:23,160 --> 00:00:27,920
别着急 我们这里还有很多有趣的照片
Don't worry. We have many interesting photographs.

12
00:00:28,040 --> 00:00:29,840
怎么了?
What's wrong?

13
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,520
弗兰克 我喜欢上别人了 我要搬出去了
Frank, I've met someone. I'm moving out.

14
00:00:33,680 --> 00:00:34,994
康 你居然出卖我! 
You set me up, Kang!  

15
00:00:34,995 --> 00:00:36,440
不然他们会吊死我的!
They were gonna hang me!

16
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:40,560
- 我们完了 - 我们早完了 山姆!
- We're done. - We've been done for a while, Sam!

17
00:00:40,720 --> 00:00:44,240
我想找山姆 但他还没有回来
I was supposed to meet Sam. He hasn't come back yet.

18
00:00:44,400 --> 00:00:46,240
你确定想看他这个样子?
You're sure you want to see this?

19
00:00:47,320 --> 00:00:48,800
他还好吗?
Is he alright?

20
00:00:48,960 --> 00:00:50,600
至少好几个小时他哪儿都去不了
He won't be going anywhere for a few hours.

21
00:00:50,760 --> 00:00:53,360
最好让他在这里睡一觉
Better to just let him sleep it off here.

22
00:02:22,060 --> 00:02:27,060
石龙岗之路 第一季第08集


23
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:38,440
你想谈谈这事吗?
Do you want to talk about it?

24
00:02:41,240 --> 00:02:42,720
山姆?
Sam?

25
00:02:42,880 --> 00:02:45,720
你看 我已经道过歉了 但你要明白...
Look, I said I'm sorry, but, you know...

26
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:48,920
- 嘿 你当时完全失去意识了
- Hey.You were completely unconscious.

27
00:02:51,700 --> 00:02:53,700
又不是每天都会这样
It's not like it happens every day.

28
00:02:53,860 --> 00:02:56,420
你也知道 我遇到你之后就再没碰过了
You know, I haven't touched it since we met.

29
00:02:56,580 --> 00:02:59,100
但你昨晚又开始了
But you chose last night to start again.

30
00:03:00,100 --> 00:03:01,580
我们说好了
We had an arrangement.

31
00:03:01,740 --> 00:03:03,820
- 我们约好见面的 - 没错
- We were meant to meet. - Yeah.

32
00:03:06,580 --> 00:03:09,380
你要说的就这些?
That's all you're going to say about it?

33
00:03:13,820 --> 00:03:16,660
康走私炸药被抓了
Kang was caught smuggling explosives.

34
00:03:16,780 --> 00:03:20,420
我意思是... 他说他是被陷害的
I mean... he said he was set up.

35
00:03:22,700 --> 00:03:25,660
我信了他 结果一个无辜的人被杀害了
And because I believed him, an innocent man was shot.

36
00:03:25,820 --> 00:03:30,100
为什么你不等等 和我商量一下呢?
Why didn't you wait, talk to me about it?

37
00:03:34,300 --> 00:03:36,860
我们不是要一起吗?
We're together, aren't we?

38
00:03:38,861 --> 00:03:39,820
当然了
Of course we are.

39
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:46,160
听着 你还打算告诉弗兰克吗?
Listen, you still plan on telling Frank?

40
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:49,880
山姆! 辛普森夫人
Sam! Mrs Simpson.

41
00:03:50,040 --> 00:03:52,920
打扰了 有一个澳大利亚外交官在侦探所等你
Sorry, there's an Australian diplomat at the agency.

42
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:55,160
- 能等会吗? - 恐怕不行
- Can it wait? - Not really.

43
00:03:56,160 --> 00:03:59,440
去吧 去吧 稍后我再来找你
Go, go. Um... I'll come back later.

44
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:18,638
郑夫人 希望你能理解 
As you can understand, 

45
00:04:18,639 --> 00:04:20,600
这件事您必须优先处理
this has to take complete priority, Mrs Cheng.

46
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:24,600
山姆 这是澳大利亚大使馆的安德森先生
Sam. You know Mr Anderson from Australian Embassy.

47
00:04:24,760 --> 00:04:26,760
- 斯图尔特 - 天哪 山姆你看起来真糟
- Stuart. - God, Sam, you look like hell.

48
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:29,600
如果我知道你来 就会花时间打理一下了
If I'd known you were gonna be here, I would've made the effort.

49
00:04:29,760 --> 00:04:31,640
听说你弄丢了几个澳大利亚女孩
Heard you lost a couple of Australian girls.

50
00:04:31,760 --> 00:04:33,120
什么? 不 我没有...
What? No, I didn't...

51
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:35,880
她们在一艘开往伦敦的货船上
They were on a freighter, bound for London.

52
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:37,425
安德森先生本打算去接应 
Mr Anderson was to meet them 

53
00:04:37,426 --> 00:04:38,580
然后让她们乘飞机回国
and send them on a plane home,

54
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:40,360
但是他到了之后她们都不见了
but they were gone when he arrived.

55
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:42,560
什么时候外交官们开始关注起观光客了?
Since when do diplomats babysit tourists?

56
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:45,000
因为其中一个女孩是加里・艾奎斯特的女儿
Since one of the girls was Gary Edquist's daughter.

57
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:46,320
艾奎斯特?
Edquist?

58
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:49,360
我想他拥有你们北部国土的一半面积
I believe he owns half of your Northern Territory,

59
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:51,040
可对土地任意取舍
give or take an acre.

60
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,120
她当时是在货船上旅行吗?
What was she doing travelling on a freighter?

61
00:04:52,121 --> 00:04:53,926
她老爸都可以买只班轮了  
Dad could have bought a liner.  

62
00:04:54,327 --> 00:04:56,700
显然 她老爸并不知情
Apparently, Daddy did not know.

63
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:58,400
干得不错呢
Well, good for her.

64
00:04:58,560 --> 00:05:01,720
我们还是告诉她老爸只在乎他的生意算了!
I mean, come on, tell her old man to mind his own business!

65
00:05:01,840 --> 00:05:03,200
这样问题就解决了 哈?
Problem solved, huh?

66
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:05,320
轮船靠岸时这些女孩并不在船上
The girls weren't on the ship when it docked.

67
00:05:05,480 --> 00:05:08,640
海关也没有她们在新加坡上岸的记录
And Customs has no record of disembarkation in Singapore.

68
00:05:09,960 --> 00:05:13,280
还有她老爸是首相的密友
And her father is a close friend of the Prime Minister.

69
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:16,040
不是吧
Oh, for fuck's sake.

70
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:18,720
我们必须找到这些女孩
We have to find the girls.

71
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:39,120
卡米拉・艾奎斯特 19岁
Camilla Edquist. 19.

72
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:41,680
已被悉尼大学法律系录取
She's been accepted into law at Sydney Uni.

73
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:43,160
她朋友呢?
Who's her friend?

74
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:44,920
吉娜・克肖
Gina Kershaw.

75
00:05:45,080 --> 00:05:47,120
消防局炊事员的女儿
She's the daughter of the station cook.

76
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:48,800
她们一块长大
The girls grew up together.

77
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:51,320
好吧 我们去找这个船长谈谈
Right, let's talk to this captain.

78
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:56,640
你最后一次见到她们是什么时候?
When was the last time you saw them?

79
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:57,640
晚饭时间
Dinner time.

80
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:59,034
她们像往常一样 
They grabbed their food 

81
00:05:59,035 --> 00:06:01,040
拿了吃的到她们的船舱里去吃
and took off to their cabin, just like always.

82
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:03,120
你和她们聊得来吗? 喜欢她们吗?
Did you get on with them? Did you like 'em?

83
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:06,280
我不必和她们套近乎 她们只是付费的乘客
I don't have to get on with them. They were paying passengers.

84
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:07,760
我喜欢的是她们的钱
I like their money.

85
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:10,000
所以你也想不出她们的去向?
And you've got no idea where they could be?

86
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:12,360
不知道 问完了吗?
No. We done?

87
00:06:12,480 --> 00:06:13,840
完了
Yeah.

88
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:19,200
我半小时后加燃油
I'm bunkering fuel in half an hour.

89
00:06:19,320 --> 00:06:21,120
在太阳落山前开船
We cast off by sunset.

90
00:06:25,640 --> 00:06:28,560
看 她们不在这儿 你满意了吧?
Oh, look, they're not here. You happy?

91
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:31,760
我们不应该去唐人街找她们吗?
Look, shouldn't we be in Chinatown trying to find them?

92
00:06:31,880 --> 00:06:33,760
有人去那看过了
Someone's had a go at that.

93
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:36,320
这是什么?
What?

94
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:38,800
看来有人曾尝试把这门踢开
Looks like someone's tried to kick the door in.

95
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:41,360
你想说什么?
What are you saying?

96
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:43,920
或许什么都不是 是这船太旧了
It may be nothing. It's an old boat.

97
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:47,080
听着 大使答应了艾奎斯特先生
Look, the ambassador promised Mr Edquist

98
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:48,640
而我答应了大使
and I promised the ambassador.

99
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:51,400
- 你报警了吗? - 什么? 没有
- Did you alert the Singapore police? - What? No.

100
00:06:51,520 --> 00:06:52,880
我不认为...
Look, I didn't think...

101
00:06:53,040 --> 00:06:56,400
这些女孩可能只是想去城里 去观光旅游
The girls have probably just gone into town. They've gone sightseeing.

102
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:58,280
那她们为什么要带行李?
So why did they take their luggage?

103
00:06:59,280 --> 00:07:02,920
大概是要待在新加坡又不想告诉其他人
Maybe they decided to stay in Singapore and not tell anyone.

104
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:04,800
所以偷偷地过了海关
Snuck past Customs.

105
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:06,280
或许吧
Maybe.

106
00:07:06,440 --> 00:07:08,840
她们知道你是来带她们回国的吗?
Did they know that you were coming to send 'em home?

107
00:07:08,860 --> 00:07:10,320
不知道
No.

108
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:12,460
那么 为什么她们要溜走? 
Well, why did they sneak off, then? 

109
00:07:12,461 --> 00:07:13,680
为什么不过海关?
Why not go through Customs?

110
00:07:15,640 --> 00:07:18,120
给我一小时时间 如果我还找不到她们...
Give me an hour. If I can't find them...

111
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:19,880
我马上报警
I'll call the police.

112
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:17,440
你是谁? 你想干什么?
Who are you? What do you want?

113
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:20,920
- 你是帕特丽夏・郑? - 你是谁?
- You're Patricia Cheng? - Who are you?

114
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:24,840
我是美玲 我...
I'm Mei Ling. I...

115
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:28,200
- 我们能去别处谈谈吗? - 谈什么?
- Can we go somewhere to talk? - About what?

116
00:08:28,320 --> 00:08:31,120
这附近有个茶社
There's a tea house around here.

117
00:08:31,280 --> 00:08:34,120
- 我有话要说... - 就在这儿说吧
- What I have to say... - You can say it right here.

118
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:41,360
我见过你丈夫... 就在他出事的那晚
I saw your husband... on the night he died.

119
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:43,720
你看到了?
Did you see it?

120
00:08:43,880 --> 00:08:46,720
- 你知道发生什么事了吗? - 不知道
- Do you know what happened? - No.

121
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:48,280
然后呢?
Then what?

122
00:08:49,840 --> 00:08:53,200
那晚早些时候 我们在一起
We were together, earlier in the night.

123
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:55,680
在一起?
Together?

124
00:08:56,680 --> 00:09:00,320
你是他的客户... 还是朋友?
You were a client... or friend?

125
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:03,240
比朋友更近一些
More than friends.

126
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:06,920
我是在周怡家工作的时候认识他的
We met each other when I worked at Joo Ee's.

127
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:11,040
我生了他的孩子
I had his baby.

128
00:09:11,160 --> 00:09:12,520
一个男孩
A boy.

129
00:09:12,640 --> 00:09:14,240
已经四岁了
He's four now.

130
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:18,600
以前温斯顿抚养他
Winston used to provide for him.

131
00:09:18,760 --> 00:09:21,198
可自从他死了... 
But since his death... 

132
00:09:21,199 --> 00:09:23,880
我已经花光了所有的积蓄
I've run out of all my savings.

133
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:26,000
我没有其他人可以依靠了
I've no-one else to turn to.

134
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:37,640
你真无耻 你个下流的骗子
You have no sense of shame.You dirty liar.

135
00:09:38,640 --> 00:09:40,240
那块手表
The watch.

136
00:09:40,400 --> 00:09:42,760
七月份我放在你家门阶上了
I left it on your doorstep during Seventh Month.

137
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:47,400
如果你再跟着我 我就报警了
If you follow me again, I'll call the police.

138
00:09:58,400 --> 00:09:59,400
大娘
Aunty.


139
00:09:59,501 --> 00:10:01,400
我需要你帮忙


140
00:10:01,401 --> 00:10:02,401
给我你的手


141
00:10:02,820 --> 00:10:05,420
今天你想要什么消息?
What you want today?

142
00:10:05,540 --> 00:10:07,180
我正在寻找两个白人女孩
I'm looking for two white girls.

143
00:10:08,300 --> 00:10:09,580
山姆 小心你的小命
Samboy, your heart.

144
00:10:09,740 --> 00:10:11,740
他们是澳大利亚人 从猎户星船登岸
They're Australians, off the Orion Star.

145
00:10:11,900 --> 00:10:14,020
- 或许带着手提箱 背包 - 没看到
- Probably got suitcases, rucksacks. - No see.

146
00:10:14,140 --> 00:10:16,500
那你有看到任何船员吗?
Have you seen any crew off the ship?

147
00:10:17,500 --> 00:10:19,820
- 山姆 真为你感到难过 - 行了
- Big sadness for you, Samboy.- Yeah, OK.

148
00:10:19,980 --> 00:10:21,503
你到底有没有看到船上的人?  
Have you seen any crew off the ship? 

149
00:10:21,504 --> 00:10:22,620
我没开玩笑 我是认真的
I no joke. This serious.

150
00:10:22,840 --> 00:10:23,840
我也是认真的
I'm serious too.

151
00:10:24,340 --> 00:10:27,100
- 猎户星船? - 没错
- Orion Star? - Yeah.

152
00:10:27,220 --> 00:10:29,860
好吧 好吧 我知道
Yeah, yeah, yeah, I know, I know.

153
00:10:29,980 --> 00:10:31,340
你给多少钱?
How much it worth?

154
00:10:52,340 --> 00:10:54,340
快跑 快!
Run, run, run!

155
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:58,220
离开这里!
Get out of here!

156
00:11:00,700 --> 00:11:03,380
他们是猎户星船的人吗?
These guys off the Orion Star?

157
00:11:03,540 --> 00:11:05,380
只有那个人是
Just that guy.

158
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:12,856
先生? 在你杀了这小子之前 
Gentlemen? Mind if I have a word with this bloke 

159
00:11:12,857 --> 00:11:13,540
介意我和他说两句吗?
before you kill him?

160
00:11:13,660 --> 00:11:15,220
滚远点儿
Stay out of it.

161
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:21,700
来啊!
Come on!

162
00:11:31,340 --> 00:11:34,260
- 你就是杰克? - 是啊
- Your name Jack? - Yeah.

163
00:11:44,340 --> 00:11:47,660
你出现的时候 我正好恢复元气了
I just about got my second wind when you showed up.

164
00:11:47,820 --> 00:11:49,140
还是谢谢你了
Thanks anyway.

165
00:11:49,300 --> 00:11:52,260
没什么的 那 说说这些女孩子吧
Oh, don't mention it.So, these girls, you were saying?

166
00:11:52,380 --> 00:11:55,780
好 大部分时间
Yeah. Oh, kept to themselves.

167
00:11:55,940 --> 00:11:58,940
她们都自己呆着 
You know, most of the time.

168
00:11:59,060 --> 00:12:00,780
那剩下的时间呢?
How about the rest of the time?

169
00:12:00,940 --> 00:12:03,180
你应该和霍克谈谈
You ought to talk to Hawk about that.

